                                         CAPE TOWN - Three suspects have been arrested on suspicion of being involved in a shooting in Mitchells Plain.  When police arrived at a local garage n Saturday, three men were shot and wounded. Police say one of the suspects also handed in his firearm.  The city’s Wayne Dyason says officials are investigating. “One of the injured suspects handed his firearm to another accomplice who disappeared in the crowd. Three suspects were arrested and taken to hospital under police guard.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)